        ated:learningTheories ,
        ated:nonverbalAbility ;
    skos:scopeNote "Theory or view of human intellect, originated in 1983 by Howard Gardner, that every individual has at least seven different autonomous intelligences, i.e. linguistic, logical-mathematical, spatial, bodily-kinesthetic, musical, interpersonal, and intrapersonal - more recently, an eighth intelligence (naturalist) has been recognised, and a ninth (existential) is being considered"@en ;
.

